  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 19:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] VWAP Redeemed: +30pp Delta on n=250 \u2014 Remove Decision REVERSED\n\n**Task:** Analyze 19h conviction failures + deep indicator re-analysis on full dataset.\n\n**19h result:** No trades. Bias briefly negative (-50 to -58) but LOW_CONVICTION (2/4). OBI\u274c + VWAP\u274c blocking consistently. Regime settled to MIXED 3/6.\n\n**VWAP FINDING REVERSED (was -3pp \u2192 now +30pp):**\n\nFull dataset (n=250, zombie-contaminated but indicative):\n| Indicator | \u2705 WR | \u274c WR | Delta |\n|-----------|-------|-------|-------|\n| OBI | 66% | 63% | +3pp |\n| CVD | 61% | **88%** | **-27pp (INVERTED!)** |\n| MACD | 65% | 63% | +2pp |\n| **VWAP** | **69%** | **39%** | **+30pp** |\n\nV4.1 active hours only (n=77, cleaner):\n| Indicator | \u2705 WR | \u274c WR | Delta |\n|-----------|-------|-------|-------|\n| OBI | 85% | 71% | +14pp |\n| CVD | 74% | **94%** | **-20pp (INVERTED!)** |\n| MACD | 78% | 75% | +3pp |\n| **VWAP** | **79%** | **50%** | **+29pp** |\n\n**VWAP is the SECOND strongest indicator (+29-30pp delta). Do NOT remove.**\nThe overnight -3pp finding was from n=2 VWAP\u274c samples \u2014 pure noise.\n\n**CVD IS INVERTED in full dataset:**\nCVD\u274c (negative) = 88-94% WR (better than CVD\u2705!)\nThis means high negative CVD (strong selling pressure) = GREAT for contrarian YES\nThe current implementation CORRECTLY uses CVD< threshold as \u2705\nSo CVD scoring is fine \u2014 it's just that CVD\u274c trades are actually BETTER quality\n\n**V5b spec REVISION NEEDED:**\n- KEEP VWAP in scoring (was \"remove\")\n- Consider CVD weighting differently (CVD\u274c = better)\n- OBI delta is +14pp in clean hours, not +36pp as overnight found\n- MACD delta is essentially noise (2-3pp)\n\n**19h conviction pattern today:** OBI\u274c + VWAP\u274c = consistent across all 19h signals. Both are meaningful signals saying \"trend hasn't reversed yet.\" The bot correctly blocked.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 23:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] Shadow Tracker Enhanced: Regime + V5a Fields Added\n\n**Task:** Add regime score and V5a pass status to shadow trade entries for conditional analysis.\n\n**Change:** `scripts/shadow-trade-tracker-v2.sh` now includes:\n- `regime`: RANGE/TREND/STRONG_TREND (from regime-detector.py --json)\n- `regime_score`: 0-6 (numeric)\n- `v5a_pass`: boolean (would signal pass |bias| \u2265 45?)\n\n**Test entry:**\n```json\n{\"ts\":\"2026-03-31T23:39:04\",\"hour\":23,\"bias\":55.5,\"regime\":\"TREND\",\"regime_score\":4,\"v5a_pass\":false}\n```\n\n**Why this matters:** Today's raw shadow WR = 49% (n=45). But that's unfiltered. The KEY question for V6 is: **do excluded hours with RANGE regime have higher WR?**\n\nIf regime-filtered shadow trades at excluded hours hit 60%+ WR, conditional hour expansion is viable (e.g., add 10h/16h but ONLY when regime \u2264 3/6).\n\n**Analysis timeline:**\n- Apr 1-7: Collect regime-tagged shadow data\n- Apr 7: Run conditional WR analysis\n- Apr 14: V6 decision on hour expansion\n\n**Today's entry count:** This is entry #44 in the WORKLOG for Mar 31.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 23:08 UTC \u2014 [",
